                            <comment id="285835" author="adilger" created="Mon, 23 Nov 2020 23:22:40 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Bobijam, could you please take a look at this patch and refresh it.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I think we are still seeing similar problems under heavy load.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="231029" author="adilger" created="Sat, 28 Jul 2018 02:59:13 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;On a related note, if there is heavy random read traffic on a large input file that is causing high IOPS and slowdown, you could consider to use &quot;&lt;tt&gt;lfs ladvise willread /path/to/file&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; to prefetch the into RAM on the OST(s) it is located on. This requires that the input file is striped across enough OSTs to fit into RAM. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
